network_overview: The trace shows two independent control-plane exchanges: a GTPv2-C Create/Delete Bearer dialog (TEID 0xb43a333b) that ends with an unknown cause value 209, and two Diameter CCR exchanges on TCP/3868 returning result codes 2001 and 4010. No user-plane or voice/IMS traffic is present.

observations.finding: Create Session Request (msg 0x10) answered with Delete Bearer Response (msg 0x11) carrying unknown cause 209
One Diameter CCR terminated with permanent failure 4010 (DIAMETER_END_USER_SERVICE_DENIED)
All observed traffic is control-plane; no GTP-U or RTP packets captured
observations.evidence: Protocols detected list: Diameter, GTP-C only

root_causes.issue: GTP-C bearer setup rejected with proprietary cause
root_causes.description: The MME/SGW attempted to create a bearer (msg 0x10) but the peer responded with a Delete Bearer Response containing an undocumented cause value 209, indicating a vendor-specific rejection or internal error.
root_causes.impact: Bearer context not established; user-plane tunnel unavailable

root_causes.issue: Diameter policy denial for one subscriber session
root_causes.description: A Diameter CCR request was answered with result-code 4010 (DIAMETER_END_USER_SERVICE_DENIED), indicating the PCRF or OCS refused service activation for that subscriber.
root_causes.impact: Subscriber cannot activate the requested service/PDN connection
evidence_refs: Diameter frame 5: CCA answer with result-code=4010

inconclusive_aspects.reason: No SIP, RTP, or IMS protocols observed
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Capture on SBC or P-CSCF interface including SIP and RTP

inconclusive_aspects.reason: Cause value 209 is not defined in 3GPP TS 29.274
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Vendor-specific logs from the replying node (SGW/PGW) or GTP-C trace with private extension AVPs

inconclusive_aspects.reason: GTP-U tunnels present in flow stats but zero GTP-U packets captured
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Mirror the S1-U or S5-U interface to observe GTP-U traffic

recommendations.action: Consult vendor documentation for GTP-C cause 209 and upgrade firmware if a known bug
recommendations.rationale: Undocumented cause values often indicate software defects or configuration mismatches

recommendations.action: Check PCRF/OCS subscriber profile for the IMSI that received Diameter result 4010
recommendations.rationale: Permanent Diameter failure 4010 indicates service not allowed for that user

recommendations.action: Capture on S1-U/S5-U to confirm whether user-plane packets use the advertised TEID 0xb43a333b
recommendations.rationale: Bearer creation may have failed silently even though a TEID was allocated

session_analysis.signaling_health: Mixed: one GTP-C procedure failed with unknown cause 209; one Diameter CCR succeeded (2001) and one failed (4010); no retransmissions detected
session_analysis.user_plane_health: Not observable: GTP-U tunnels listed but zero GTP-U packets captured
session_analysis.voice_quality: Not observable: no RTP or IMS protocols present
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: No correlation possible: user-plane not captured and no SIP/RTP observed
